oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Governor Gordon Browning speech - 1952-05-29
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: First recording contains excerpts of a rebroadcast of a speech given by King George VI of England in regards to D-Day. Second recording contains excerpts of a speech given by Governor Gordon Browning on May 29, 1952 on radio station WMC-AM (Radio station : Memphis, Tenn.)
